  "plot outline": "PK (Dorff), an English orphan terrorised for his family's political beliefs in Africa, turns to his only friend, a kindly world-wise prisoner, Geel Piet (Freeman). Geel teaches him how to box with the motto \"fight with your fists and lead with your heart\". As he grows to manhood, PK uses these words to take on the system and the injustices he sees around him - and finds that one person really can make a difference.",
